FSharpFunc<T, TResult> SpecificCallPattern(FSharpExpr templateParameter)

A parameterized active pattern to recognize calls to a specified function or method. The returned elements are the optional target object (present if the target is an instance method), the generic type instantation (non-empty if the target is a generic instantiation), and the arguments to the function or method.
Parameters
FSharpExpr templateParameter

The input template expression to specify the method to call.

Return
FSharpFunc<T, TResult>

The optional target object (present if the target is an instance method), the generic type instantation (non-empty if the target is a generic instantiation), and the arguments to the function or method.
